President Muhammadu Buhari in a speech addressing the nation on Monday extended the lockdown by one week in Lagos, Abuja, and Ogun state amid the coronavirus pandemic. However, he stated that there will be a gradual easing of the lockdown: “The lockdown in the FCT, Lagos & Ogun States shall subsist remain in place until these new ones come into effect on Saturday, 2nd May 2020 at 9 am,” The president after the expiration of the lockdowm, there will be a national “curfew from 8 pm to 6 am.” Read More: Full text of President Buhari’s third national broadcast on coronavirus He further stated that there will be no social and religious gatherings and “mandatory use of face masks or coverings in public in addition to maintaining physical distancing and personal hygiene.” This has since stirred several conversations online with people airing their opinion. See some reactions below:         